---
title: "About — macapinlac.com"
description: "About Ritchie Macapinlac — tech professional, parent, and serial rebuilder of perfectly functional things based in Vancouver, BC."
---
<% content_for :body_attrs do %>data-screen-label="About"<% end %>

<div class="wrap">
  <div class="ahero">
    <div class="portrait">
      <%= image_tag 'avatar-240.webp', alt: 'Ritchie Macapinlac' %>
      <span class="badge">📍 vancouver, bc</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="eyebrow"><span class="c">$</span> whoami --verbose</div>
      <h1>A tech professional, parent, and serial rebuilder of <em>perfectly functional</em> things.</h1>
      <p class="lede">This site has been my online home since 2000 — which makes me older than dirt itself.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>I write about technology, parenting, productivity, and my well-documented tendency to over-engineer everything. By day I work in tech — a long career somewhere between DevOps, infrastructure, and "can you take a look at this?" By night and weekend, I tinker: a homelab nobody asked for, a money system only I understand, and the occasional EV road trip planned with the enthusiasm of a man who really loves a spreadsheet.</p>

    <p>The writing here is honest, occasionally funny, and frequently about lessons learned the hard way. You'll find earnest reflection sitting right next to a dry punchline. <strong>My wife questions most of these life choices</strong> and she's usually right.</p>

    <p>If something on this site looks broken, there's a good chance I "improved" it last weekend. This is my playground. Damnit.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="holes">
    <h2>Where I tend to wander</h2>
    <p class="sub">// the recurring obsessions, roughly</p>
    <div class="hgrid">
      <% about_page_tags.each do |tag| %>
        <% slug = tag.name.downcase.gsub(/\s+/, '-') %>
        <a class="hole" href="/tags/<%= slug %>.html">
          <span class="em"><%= tag.icon %></span>
          <div>
            <div class="t"><%= slug %></div>
            <div class="d"><%= tag.description %></div>
          </div>
        </a>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="now">
    <div class="lbl"><%= data.now.label %></div>
    <p><%= data.now.body.html_safe %></p>
  </div>

  <div class="contact">
    <h2>Say hello</h2>
    <div class="links">
      <% data.socials.sites.each do |site| %>
        <a class="lk" href="<%= site.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <%= site.icon %> <%= site.display_name.downcase %>
        </a>
      <% end %>
      <a class="lk" href="mailto:ritchie@macapinlac.com">📧 email</a>
      <a class="lk" href="/feed.xml">📡 rss</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  "name": "Ritchie Macapinlac",
  "url": "https://macapinlac.com",
  "description": "Technology professional, parent, and lifelong learner sharing thoughts on technology, parenting, productivity, and personal development.",
  "jobTitle": "Technology Professional",
  "knowsAbout": ["Software Development", "DevOps", "Parenting", "Productivity", "Personal Development"],
  "sameAs": [<%= data.socials.sites.map { |s| "\"#{s.url}\"" }.join(', ') %>]
}
</script>
